Date:  1/7/1908
Source:  Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page:  82
Edition:
Quote:  It is owing to the thick coating of woolly hairs found on the flower-stalks and under the leaves that the name "cotton plant" is given to it. By the Maoris it was named Tikumu, which it is thought that they gave to all large-flowered celmisias.
Notes:

